On Eid al-Fitr, the First Lady and President of the United States send warm greetings to Muslims worldwide. Eid al-Fitr, also known as the "Festival of Breaking the Fast," marks the end of Ramadan, a holy month of fasting, prayer, and reflection. In these challenging times of the coronavirus pandemic, faith, family, and friends have been relied upon for guidance. The First Lady and President hope that Muslims find comfort and strength in prayer and devotion on this day. They emphasize the peace, love, and fellowship that religion brings to our lives and wish Muslims a blessed and joyous Eid al-Fitr.